We use nested loops to iterate through all possible combinations of a and b. The outer loop iterates from a to 2a, and the inner loop iterates from b to 2b. In each iteration, we determine the current character based on the modulo operation (i % 3) and append it to the result string. After the inner loop finishes, we append an 'a' to ensure the string has a length of a + b. Finally, we return the result string. This solution has a high efficiency since it only considers the given constraints and generates the required string in a single pass.

